HEADWORD: Quadrin
<hw>Quad"rin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF., fr. L.
<ets>quadrini</ets> four each, fr. <ets>quattuor</ets> four.]</ety>
<def>A small piece of money, in value about a farthing, or a half
cent.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

